Comment: "Never figured out how to safely do the top without a pad. Climbing to the lip encounter wasn't too hard."
"Had a kink in my neck and couldn't really move my head, but still did most of the moves."
"Did Thegg again! Still cannot do the first move for the life of me...maybe one day."
"Did most of the moves...individually. Hoping it feels better not in the sun next time."
"Still cannot do the first move! But Joaquin did!!"
"Couldnt figure out how to move out right"
"Wow that move to the pocket crimp is long and hard...and pogoing after would be hard too. Very cool though!"
"One day I will learn how to kneebar! Sage did it and it was really really cool!"
"Did all the moves before having to walk out"
"Tried the campus method and felt closer, but it really hurt my scapula so I stopped. Teddy and Conor did it."
"Got close and then it started raining. It's sharp"

"Should have done it on my 3rd try, then regressed, then should have done it on my ~10th try before regressing really hard and tearing open my pinky. Was pretty disappointed with my performance, but that's how it goes sometimes."

"Never did the first move, but did it (to a safe drop off point) from a move in. This is VERY crimpy and sharp. Caitlin could do the first move but not the 3rd(?) move, so combined we had a team send. Conor gave up, but then got bored and gritted his teeth and did it. It still looked hard.

In lighter news, Casey took my first witnessed Hueco dump. We collected all the plastic bags we could find and off he went, only to return after relieving himself alerting us to the fact that he couldn't find any of the bags other than the bag that the toilet paper was in. He took C^2's saucy sandwich bag for a second layer, and made the (smart) decision to sacrifice his tupperware for extra protection.

When we left the area he realized the bags were in his jacket pocket which he had removed prior to pooping. A comedy in three parts."
"Tried once and got two (2) flappers! So I stopped trying. Caitlin did it though! And Joaquin did New Religion and Sage got very close!"
"I bet this would be WAY easier with a kneebar. Too bad we didn't have a kneebar pad, nor am I able to competently kneebar."
"Couldn't do the knee bar to pull off the ground but did the rest of the problem. The top is super cool."
"Sooooo cold. Friction felt great, but every time I fell I'd kick the wall and it would hurt super bad. Conor repeated and Casey did it!"
"Still really hard. Mostly tried out of boredom and to give some sick support to Caitlin."
"Doesn't feel good on the knee but I'd like to do it. I'm bad at jumping."
"Did not feel good on the knee."
"Couldn't figure out how to get off the ground. After watching Louie's video it turned out we were starting in the wrong place."
"Got all the moves, just didn't have the juice to finish it off. Hopefully will come back tomorrow before heading out and can get it done."
"God damn this is so hard. Guess this will have to wait for another year...."
"Will I ever do this? Doubt it. Banged into the tree chimney a few times decently hard. Piano matching is so hard."

"Tried to wake up early and get better temperature; results very meh. Forgot I don't operate well this early, plus I'm tired, so this was pretty useless. Still did the top a couple of times because I'm loving that part, just that damn bump (and today the move before the bump). At least the forest is very pleasant and still at this hour!"

"Pretty depressing to keep walking back up here to fall at the same spot over and over. Kind of fully starting to lose motivation. At least the cave is usually much cooler than the rest of the forest so the temperature is pleasant. "

"Another long session of falling on basically the same two moves. Managed to do the bump a couple times in isolation, but VERY low percentage. Came close to doing the bump once from the bottom (but not really even that close, just sorta wildly slapped the crimp with my feet coming off)."
"Did not feel very good on any of those holds. Maybe a heat thing? Skin thing? Weakness thing?"
"Oof so hard. Pulled on 3 times. Foot popped 3 times. Knee scraped 3 times. Awkward and balancey to reach up to that gastony arete. Looks very cool though wish I could do it."

"Maybe the longest I sat at a boulder, got the top super dialed (brought the Futuras, which work much better than the barefoot method). Just need to link the move to the lip and the first bump. Really hoping I only have to do that once and will finish it off once that happens."
"Probably wouldn't feel too bad with an extra pad or two and/or a spotter. But solo with 1.5 pads is too scary for me."

"Whoa! Did much better than expected. Did every move but the first bump (this has gotta be the crux right? Not the move to the jug?) and was semi-close on that a couple times. No left shoe for the heel hook, kind of crazy but the Solutions just have way too insensitive of a heel for that for me."

"Started to rain lightly but the top hold stayed pretty dry so it was okay. What wasn't okay was how much I needed to poop. Each time I jumped I was slightly afraid a little poo would come out (none did, I made it home in time)."

"The crux move is so hard! Reach for an undercling crimp thing above your head. Wish it was not so hot and humid when I tried this so I would know whether or not it was actually possible. Would love to be able to do this someday though, even if the approach isn't my favorite."

"After doing Flow Stone and checking this out this morning, I went home and watched some videos of this to gauge whether it would be worth going back to. After sitting around for a few hours the weather had cooled down I couldn't think of anything else to do so I drove back out there to give it some goes. It was decently scary trying to figure out the mid/top section with 2 pads, but almost doable. However it was pretty sharp, and harder than I thought, so overall a 2.5/5 experience. Would consider going back, but probably not solo."
"Couldn't hold onto a single hold really."
"So fun, wish I could have done it, if only it wasn't soooo crowded."
"Did the first move once. Did no other moves. Felt impossible (possibly heat? But also just very hard and anti-style)"
"Matching the lip hurt my wrist. Will have to go back in a week or so when it feels better hopefully and finish it off."
"Got all the moves at the end of the day. Not enough skin/energy/strength to put it all together, but it's possible which I wasn't sure about before!"

"I am starting to think I will never ever do this. It's so hard. I've never gotten more than ~18 inches of the ground. Felt kind of close once though, but then I dry fired bad and my fingies stung for like 20 minutes."
"Never got off the ground really. The foot is very high and I am not good at that. I'm not good at much in climbing these days, but this is certainly near the top of the list."
"Heel the arete to reach back far right, would really like another 4 inches of wingspan."
"I suck at this. The other beta is easily but much less pleasant so I'll stick with the original."
"Eh, maybe I'll stay on the wall one day. Maybe not."

"Better conditions, but waaaay worse skin. I think the skin/fatigue canceled out the cooler weather. This one might just have to wait. It kind of feels likeThe Fury, it's just a game of chance (aka I'm not strong enough to do it super clean, so I just have to get lucky once)."
"Did each move individually. Did not do them together. Very hot and sweaty. Lots of dirtbikers going mach dick past, was kind of afraid a rock would kick up and kill me."
"Absolute insanity. Could barely get off the ground, never latched the second hold, never even managed to try the fun dyno. Maybe it'll be better when it's less hot and humid."
"Damn. Thought today was the day but wasn't meant to be. Even tried a basketball shoe for extra jumping, but that just made it harder. Maybe I was never as close as I thought..."
"Well I did what I thought was the crux, and then had no idea what to do after so I guess that's something. Maybe wearing shoes that had a more precise heel could have been helpful, but who knows."

"I thought this innovative heel beta I saw a video on was going to be the difference. It wasn't. Underclings are still way too hard. My down jacket did blow away in a strong gust of wind though so that added some excitement. I think a gust whipped through the cave and rocketed out; my jacket flew up and out of the cave, probably like 40-70 feet up in the air. I thought I was going to have to spend the rest of the day looking for it, but luckily I found it after maybe 25 (stressful) minutes. It had blown maybe ~250 feet east and I audibly shrieked when I found it. Probably happier to find the jacket than to do any climb, so I'll take it."

"Was joined by a large crew (Jeff and 4 of his friends). The number of pads helped, but my index fingers were pretty tender from Predator I think? DFinally did the first move but felt a little tweak so called it good for the day. "I know we just met, but you need to set higher goals for yourself." Thank you random *EXTREMELY* strong girl, I think that's a pretty good assessment of my goal setting mentality."
"Did not make a lot of progress, but did crumble a foothold."
"I WANT TO DO THIS SO BAD. WHY IS JUMPING SO HARD."
"Tried out some of the moves, but realized I had neither the skin nor the energy to do much more than that."
"Couldn't figure out how to do the punchy undercling move, felt really far."
"Sunny and lot, the first crimp (not very sharp) started to give me a split. Also felt pretty hard."

"Ran into Matt and new friend Jeff and gave it a couple tries with them. Try 1: should have flashed, but did not think about how to do topout. Try 22: did top section in isolation (not very hard). Then I sat around and ate and when I tried again I felt like jello and could not do the second move. Returning home I've realized that I think we were using bad beta (no high right heel for second move). Maybe it will feel even easier with that method when I go back."
"It's a 3 move problem and I've done 0 moves (maybe am close on the first 2?), but it's kind of fun and interesting!"
"Okay, new beta again, use TWO kneebars. Should have done it once but punted the top. Should have taken shoes off so I could feel the heel. Also maybe practice the top?"

"Maaaaybe would be doable with good skin and a lot of work, but probably best to wait. Tried the top finishing V4 problem briefly too and it was a bit sharp/stabby/not super fun; I feel bad for anybody who falls there after doing the bottom."
"The second move is the hardest single move in all of rock climbing."
"I GOT CLOSE! Very exciting! Beta: One step runup (accuracy more important than power), jump off right foot."
"Maybe got better knee bar beta this time to skip the hold our right? Felt harder than last time maybe."
"Guess what? This still felt sharp, but at least I didn't decapitate my finger this time. Maybe it'll feel better some time when it's colder."
"Have no idea how to go right hand to the crimp \_(?)_/"
"Worked out the intermediate beta, which will work way better than the jump beta for me."
"Really did not want to dyno, kept trying a myriad of other/worse options. Next time I should just jump."

"Fuck I want to be able to dyno so bad. Why are the most fun looking climbs dynos and flatwalls, two things I suck at? Slapped ~3 inches before the jug once. Key beta, wear tennis shoes (easier to jump in/more comfortable to land on)."
"What in the fuck?! This feels so hard. Got absolutely no where. According to Stupid Strong Southern Sean, this thing is just super hard."
"Would have liked to feel how the 2nd and 3rd holds feel without tape on my critical fingers. Still may be too hard for my current strength level."
"Didn't make any more progress, and I still don't want to hold that sharp hold. Probably out of my league for now."
"Juuuuuust spanny enough to make that second move blind and quite hard. Tried Casey's right method once but the foot felt even higher and balancey."
"Tried while Vanessa did Daily Dick Dose. Did all the moves but didn't finish yet."
"Did all the moves but didn't finish yet. Using a knee pad will be very helpfu."
"Almost flashed, but got tunnel finish and thrutched for the top, slicing open my middle finger. Tried to do it with tape but was too painful."
"Upon returning home I was informed that matching the loaf was bad beta by the stupidly strong man with questionable sequencing. Instead, you should flip the J."
"Very sharp, made me not want to try to hold the pocket, but at least it was a little separated from the rest of the tour."
"Felt really slippery even though it was super cold. Also realized it's not over after the first move, matching or getting your foot up to go left is going to be hard as well."
"Hooooly mosquitos. Couldn't see the top hold because of sun, think it will go next time."
"Too scary for a little boy like me! Sage put on his big boy pants"
"Slapped the hold a couple times before busting off and opening my knuckle. I don't think I can do this in the hot weather."
"Slapped the hold once surprisingly. Had taken a couple months off climbing but surprisingly felt okay on crimps and skin didn't hurt too bad. Who knows why."
"Need to work on that crimp lock-off strength. Slapped the second hold a number of times, but never with enough control to stay on."
"Did the first move! Then was too scared to really do anything else. I have become even more of a pansy than I was in the past."

"Man...I didn't expect this to be as spooky as it was. I don't know if the new landing zone makes it better or worse, but the tree is  really bothersome to me. I did the first move a couple times, but haven't quite figured out the match. I tried starting from both hands on the lip off the tree, but couldn't commit to doing any moves even with the tree padded up. Maybe this one will have to wait until I'm waaaay stronger or something."
"Super spanny...not sure if I have the reach, or if I just need to be real strong. Also I tried the normal start a couple times and have 0 idea how I did it whenever that was."
"Still don't really know how the hell to do this...At least I did *one* move this time. No idea how to get out of the full span after the first move."
"Got basically to the rock scar, and then decided it was not an ideal time to try due to traffic/0 spotters. I was pleasantly surprised how nicely the bottom section climbs."

"Got all the moves up until the upper section of Big Deal (felt lazy, didn't want to set up pads), despite feeling very sore and my skin hurting from not climbing, so that was a very pleasant surprise! Maybe I'm not as weak as I thought (though I'm sure linking them all together and then doing the upper part of Big Deal is going to be harder than I anticipate)."
"Too scared to do the topout section without a spotter or more pads. I'm not out here to get hurt!"

"Once again, too scared to do the topout section without a spotter or way more pads. Made it to the first sloper on the lip (supposedly crux), but getting to the second sloper seemed like it had higher backsplat-on-to-rock potential than what I was hoping for."
"Tried pulling on a few times and slapped the first move but couldn't keep my feet. Then realized that my skin hurt real bad and didn't want to grab more crimps."
"Maybe not the best solo boulder? Kept falling and ending up on the ground. Plus I couldn't really figure out wtf to do after getting the crimp."
"Felt surprisingly okay for not having climbed in a while. Def need some more finger strength/skin."
"Very confusing, not sure how the hell to levitate off the ground."
"Never stuck the first move but was getting closer. Then it started to rain. Also maybe the first time I've gotten use out of a kneebar?! Might even be *easier* with a kneepad?!"
"After climbing the stand to the lip, I figured I'd work this to the lip. Quickly figured it out and dropped off. Then I decided to try and top the stand out and fell and got hurt. Sick."

"Fuck. Climbed it to the lip, then climbed the other version (Blue Steel) to the lip, then decided to actually try to top this one out. Fell past where I should have and missed the bad, messing up my left heel/ankle. Will have to see how bad it is (walking out/driving home was pretty difficult/painful)."
"Sussed out most of the beta, felt pretty good to try hard."
"Damn. I really had hoped 2 years away from climbing outside was gonna make me a slab master."
"Got everything worked out, but then it got dark."
"Very spanny, not sure if my beta was great either."
"Tried to climb after straining my back sneezing. Went ok."
"All the excuses...back hurts, fingers hurt, don't know what the start holds are, don't know which direction to go, etc. etc. etc."
"Got really good at hitting just below the jug, but not getting the extra 2 inches to actually latch."
"Slapped the lip a couple times, but never got back to the actual hold. High feet dynos are hard."
"Never really generated in the right direction at all. High feet dynos are...still hard."
"This problem REALLY smells like dassie poop."
"Reminds me a little of Lidja's Mouth in Bishop...minus the chossiness. Broke a sizeable foot pulling on the second time and then n d decided to be done."
"Busted off the last move and fell on my face/head on my last attempt. This whole problem felt hard, and a little tweakyy on trmy right knee. Direct was easier, and maybe better?"
"Finally did the first move and then tried to chimney into the rock and scratched my arm and got very over it."
"Shiiit. Thought I was gonna do it when I quickly highpointed, then it turned out that the last move was/is stopper for me :(. At least I don't have to go back."
"Got high enough once, but was too far to the right. Couldn't figure out how to get that high again."
"Did the first move...twice! Couldn't do any other move though :/."
"Fuck slab is so hard. Tried to complete the whole boulder but this one stymied me. Right before the rain came."
""The trick with slab is to take lots of small steps." Made it to the bailout point 2/3 of the way up, top feels hard."
"Way harder than it looks. Couldn't do the first move."
